The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as co-saliency detection and proposes a novel graph convolutional network design and attention graph clustering algorithm. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves unsupervised learning and optimization, which suggests the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also uses benchmark datasets and evaluates the proposed method against state-of-the-art methods, indicating the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-categories.
